WEBVTT

00:03.250 --> 00:05.380
[ Serena Ryder's
"Got Your Number" plays ]

00:05.380 --> 00:08.830
Meredith: There's an old story
of a father who had two sons.

00:08.830 --> 00:11.750
When he knew a civil war
was about to break out,

00:11.750 --> 00:15.670
he sent one son to fight for
the North and one to the South.

00:15.670 --> 00:17.750
♪ The chains are gonna come ♪
♪ You bought my love ♪

00:17.750 --> 00:20.250
He figured
if he had sons on both sides,

00:20.250 --> 00:22.380
there'd be a better chance
one would survive...

00:22.380 --> 00:24.750
♪ Step 29 in the interspeed,
gone ♪

00:24.750 --> 00:26.250
♪ But it's too late, too late ♪

00:26.250 --> 00:27.790
♪ Change, you're gonna come ♪

00:27.790 --> 00:29.960
♪ Love is blind, but now I see ♪

00:29.960 --> 00:31.120
♪ I don't love you no more ♪

00:31.120 --> 00:33.960
♪ I got 20/20 ♪

00:33.960 --> 00:35.290
♪ Got your number ♪

00:35.290 --> 00:37.420
...because when you
fight a war at home,

00:37.420 --> 00:39.540
the casualties are
your neighbors...

00:39.540 --> 00:42.500
♪ See my lightning,
hear my thunder ♪

00:42.500 --> 00:44.670
♪ I got it, I got it, I got it,
I got your number ♪

00:44.670 --> 00:46.880
[ Alarm beeping ]

00:46.880 --> 00:49.880
...your friends, your family...

00:49.880 --> 00:51.170
♪ Don't want a ring, ring ♪

00:51.170 --> 00:52.790
♪ Don't got a ring, ring ♪

00:52.790 --> 00:54.500
♪ I don't need you anymore,
got everything, thing ♪

00:54.500 --> 00:56.040
...leaving you all alone.

00:56.040 --> 00:58.620
♪ Got your number,
I got your number ♪

00:58.620 --> 01:01.250
♪ I don't need you anymore,
got everything, thing ♪

01:01.250 --> 01:05.170
♪ Got your number,
I got your number ♪

01:05.170 --> 01:07.210
I need you
to do something.

01:07.210 --> 01:09.120
[ Exhales heavily ]
I told you I'd do it.

01:09.120 --> 01:11.920
Just separate out
the delicates.

01:11.920 --> 01:13.080
Not laundry.

01:13.080 --> 01:14.830
My thing is fun.

01:14.830 --> 01:16.790
I need you to clip an aneurysm
at the hospital.

01:16.790 --> 01:18.380
I'm on leave.

01:18.380 --> 01:20.170
Yeah, I need you
to be off leave.

01:20.170 --> 01:22.380
-No.
-Please.

01:22.380 --> 01:23.960
Come on.
It's this sweet little old nun,

01:23.960 --> 01:25.620
and she needs
open-heart surgery

01:25.620 --> 01:27.790
but she can't have it until
her brain aneurysm is clipped.

01:27.790 --> 01:30.210
It's so sad.

01:30.210 --> 01:31.670
Poor Sister Agnes.

01:31.670 --> 01:33.170
Don't "nun" me.

01:33.170 --> 01:35.290
The nun detail was a little bit
much, but please.

01:35.290 --> 01:37.620
Please. Come on. I need you.
You're the best.

01:37.620 --> 01:40.500
And don't tell me that
you don't miss the O.R.

01:40.500 --> 01:43.670
Just one little clip,
and you can scratch that itch.

01:43.670 --> 01:45.830
Just one little clip.

01:45.830 --> 01:47.710
You'll be in and out.

01:47.710 --> 01:49.920
And I'll make sure that
Owen doesn't see you.

01:49.920 --> 01:53.000
Promise.

01:54.580 --> 01:55.880
Give me 10 minutes.

01:59.920 --> 02:01.790
Morning.
Good to have you back.
Morning. Thank you.

02:01.790 --> 02:03.500
So, when I was Chief --

02:03.500 --> 02:04.710
Interim Chief.

02:06.250 --> 02:08.250
I took the liberty of
catching you up

02:08.250 --> 02:09.750
on all your backlogged
resident reports,

02:09.750 --> 02:12.210
department budgets,
supply orders, so...

02:12.210 --> 02:13.580
-I was gonna do that.
-Of course you were.

02:13.580 --> 02:15.040
I just figured,
you know, the same way

02:15.040 --> 02:17.620
you fill the tank with gas
when you return someone's car...

02:17.620 --> 02:18.710
You stole the car.

02:20.750 --> 02:21.580
You're welcome.

02:23.540 --> 02:25.250
Ah.
Look who's back.

02:25.250 --> 02:28.710
Have to say,
I thought you'd last longer.

02:28.710 --> 02:30.290
You folded quick.
I didn't fold.

02:30.290 --> 02:32.080
You're here,
aren't you?

02:32.080 --> 02:33.290
The chief didn't
fire Minnick.

02:33.290 --> 02:34.580
Dr. Webber asked me
to come back.

02:34.580 --> 02:35.500
There was no folding.

02:35.500 --> 02:37.580
If you say so.

02:41.710 --> 02:43.960
If you're into the guy,
why not just be with him?

02:43.960 --> 02:45.960
Because I don't
want to be with him.
Oh, come on.

02:45.960 --> 02:47.790
Is it because of Maggie?
She'll get over it.

02:47.790 --> 02:49.080
No.
I don't want to be with him.

02:49.080 --> 02:51.040
Okay. You do, though.
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

02:51.040 --> 02:53.880
But I don't.

02:53.880 --> 02:56.250
[ Indistinct talking
over P.A. system ]

03:01.790 --> 03:04.540
So, listen, are we cool?

03:04.540 --> 03:06.620
What do you mean,
"Are we cool?"

03:06.620 --> 03:09.290
I don't want there to be
any problems with patients.

03:09.290 --> 03:12.080
Just, are we cool?
I mean, to work together.

03:12.080 --> 03:13.790
We're cool.
[ Elevator bell dings ]

03:13.790 --> 03:16.120
I had to ask.
It's kids.

03:16.120 --> 03:17.580
We're cool.

03:17.580 --> 03:19.830
Okay. Good.

03:23.620 --> 03:25.500
The mattresses?

03:25.500 --> 03:27.830
Yes. You need to replace every
mattress in every on-call room.

03:27.830 --> 03:30.040
Unacceptable.
-He's not wrong.

03:30.040 --> 03:31.790
These mattresses
are lumpy.

03:31.790 --> 03:33.880
They're misshapen,
zero lumbar support.

03:33.880 --> 03:36.540
Our surgeons need solid rest,
not spinal damage.

03:36.540 --> 03:38.380
Noted.

03:38.380 --> 03:41.120
You might tell Dr. Webber that
if he wants to sleep soundly,

03:41.120 --> 03:44.000
he should come home and sleep
next to his bride.

03:45.670 --> 03:48.830
Uh, I'll take this
under advisement.

03:50.880 --> 03:52.040
New mattresses!

03:52.040 --> 03:54.380
Hey. You okay?

03:54.380 --> 03:55.960
No. My back hurts.

03:55.960 --> 03:57.380
Oh,
and there's nothing like

03:57.380 --> 03:59.670
having your dirty laundry aired
for everyone to see.

03:59.670 --> 04:01.040
Oh, that bad, huh?

04:01.040 --> 04:03.250
And as long as Minnick's here,
it's gonna stay bad.

04:03.250 --> 04:06.620
[ Sighs ]
I don't know what to do...

04:06.620 --> 04:09.330
except give up
and give in.

04:09.330 --> 04:11.790
No, no, that's not acceptable.
Everyone's behind you.

04:11.790 --> 04:13.670
Everyone was behind me.

04:13.670 --> 04:15.580
The longer Minnick's here,
the more people like her.

04:15.580 --> 04:16.670
And the more people like her,
then --

04:16.670 --> 04:18.460
Well, I'm behind you,
then, so just --

04:18.460 --> 04:20.460
Listen, why don't you
stay at my place?

04:20.460 --> 04:22.420
I have a guest room, and
it's got a very good mattress.

04:22.420 --> 04:25.420
I-I-It'll be fine.

04:25.420 --> 04:28.670
Arizona,
thanks for sticking with me.

04:28.670 --> 04:29.670
You're a good friend.

04:29.670 --> 04:32.040
♪♪

04:37.670 --> 04:39.620
We're losing ground.
Everybody loves Minnick.

04:39.620 --> 04:41.250
I wouldn't say that.
I mean, who said that?

04:41.250 --> 04:42.380
And now Meredith.

04:42.380 --> 04:44.000
I stood up for him
and got suspended.

04:44.000 --> 04:45.250
Yeah, and now you're back.
You rolled over.

04:45.250 --> 04:47.170
Because
he told me to come back.

04:47.170 --> 04:48.330
That's not what it looks like,
all right?

04:48.330 --> 04:49.880
You weakened
our position here.

04:49.880 --> 04:53.250
Well, we don't have a position
if he is asking us to stop.

04:53.250 --> 04:55.250
-Meredith has a point.
-The problem isn't Minnick.

04:55.250 --> 04:56.670
Maggie: The problem is that
her program is good,

04:56.670 --> 04:58.250
and now everyone knows it,
including Richard.

04:58.250 --> 04:59.330
You guys
are unbelievable.

04:59.330 --> 05:00.330
You're just gonna
abandon him now?

05:00.330 --> 05:01.670
-No. We're not.
-No.

05:01.670 --> 05:03.500
Well, I'm not gonna do that.
I'm gonna fight for him.

05:03.500 --> 05:06.250
How?
My mother's not the only Avery
in this hospital.

05:06.250 --> 05:10.830
♪♪

05:10.830 --> 05:12.580
It seems like
the colovesical fistula

05:12.580 --> 05:14.670
closed off on its own,
after all.

05:14.670 --> 05:17.460
No abdominal reconstruction
needed.

05:17.460 --> 05:20.580
Good. I was hoping to avoid
having to call Jackson in.

05:20.580 --> 05:22.290
Things still difficult
at home?

05:22.290 --> 05:24.620
[ Sighs ] I'm not sure
I can stay there anymore.

05:24.620 --> 05:28.540
I mean, I want to. It's been
so easy with Harriet, but...

05:28.540 --> 05:31.460
But everything's so much harder
than it needs to be right now.

05:31.460 --> 05:33.120
I know.
-Yeah.

05:33.120 --> 05:34.500
And...
-And what?

05:34.500 --> 05:36.880
[ Sighs ]

05:36.880 --> 05:40.580
It's just embarrassing
being demoted.

05:40.580 --> 05:41.960
You were not demoted.

05:41.960 --> 05:44.040
From Chief of General Surgery
to Trauma Attending?

05:44.040 --> 05:45.460
It looks like that.
-April, April.

05:45.460 --> 05:48.620
A title is only as good
as the person who earned it.

05:48.620 --> 05:50.420
Grey is very good,

05:50.420 --> 05:51.790
but when she wasn't here,

05:51.790 --> 05:54.040
the person they turned to
was you.

05:54.040 --> 05:55.170
Oh, I know --

05:55.170 --> 05:56.460
Do you?

05:56.460 --> 05:57.880
Then act like it.

06:03.080 --> 06:04.830
[ Baby coos ]

06:04.830 --> 06:06.920
So -- Hey.

06:06.920 --> 06:09.120
Heads, he's Leo.

06:09.120 --> 06:10.580
Let's just wait until
we know he's okay.

06:10.580 --> 06:12.040
Oh, come on. Stop.

06:12.040 --> 06:14.540
You agreed that we'd decide
with a coin toss.

06:14.540 --> 06:16.670
I noticed a systolic murmur
at the post-birth exam.

06:16.670 --> 06:18.420
It's probably nothing,
but I called just in case.

06:18.420 --> 06:21.000
I'll check it out.
DeLuca, get a pulse-ox.

06:21.000 --> 06:23.040
[ Baby crying ]

06:23.040 --> 06:25.710
Baby, our little guy
is gonna need a name --

06:25.710 --> 06:27.500
hey --
definitely before school,

06:27.500 --> 06:29.880
but probably before
we leave here, so...

06:29.880 --> 06:33.330
Heads, he's Leo,
tails, August.

06:33.330 --> 06:34.580
Okay, why is
the name I like tails?

06:34.580 --> 06:38.000
Fine.
Heads, he's August.

06:41.580 --> 06:42.620
Heads?

06:42.620 --> 06:43.750
August it is.

06:43.750 --> 06:46.500
[ Both laugh ]

06:46.500 --> 06:48.420
Pulse-ox is slightly
below normal.

06:48.420 --> 06:50.750
Yeah. Let's get some labs
and page cardio.

06:53.460 --> 06:54.330
Uh, what's happening?
Is he okay?

06:54.330 --> 06:55.710
He's got a heart murmur.

06:55.710 --> 06:57.330
I need to take him
to get some tests.

06:57.330 --> 06:59.500
I'll let you know more
as soon as I do.

06:59.500 --> 07:00.920
What's
the little guy's name?

07:00.920 --> 07:02.080
-Gus.
-Gus.

07:02.080 --> 07:04.500
-Gus.
[ Baby crying ]

07:10.380 --> 07:11.960
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

07:11.960 --> 07:13.420
Jackson:
Hey, you got a minute?

07:13.420 --> 07:16.040
Ah. Just got paged to the pit.
Can it wait?

07:16.040 --> 07:17.750
I need to talk to you
about this Minnick situation.

07:17.750 --> 07:19.790
What situation?
She's doing great.

07:19.790 --> 07:21.170
Don't pretend you don't know
what you did, Mom.

07:21.170 --> 07:22.170
People have been
fighting this

07:22.170 --> 07:23.500
since the minute
you brought her here.

07:23.500 --> 07:25.790
-Bailey brought her here.
-At your urging.

07:25.790 --> 07:27.620
And since I am the voice of
the Avery Foundation at this --

07:27.620 --> 07:29.540
Wait. I'm sorry.
You're the what?

07:29.540 --> 07:31.500
I'm the foundation's
representative on the board,

07:31.500 --> 07:33.420
right,
a position that you gave me,

07:33.420 --> 07:34.580
that you made me take.

07:34.580 --> 07:35.920
Yes,
and you kicked and screamed

07:35.920 --> 07:37.620
and whined
every step of the way.

07:37.620 --> 07:39.920
And then I took it on.

07:39.920 --> 07:42.170
So I am the Avery
of this hospital.

07:42.170 --> 07:43.580
The foundation
speaks through me.

07:43.580 --> 07:46.080
The foundation oversees.
We guide.

07:46.080 --> 07:48.380
We do not interfere
in hospital politics.

07:48.380 --> 07:50.120
How can you
say that to me?

07:50.120 --> 07:52.920
You started this by effectively
ousting Richard Webber,

07:52.920 --> 07:54.380
which, by the way,
our rank and file

07:54.380 --> 07:55.670
finds completely
unacceptable.

07:55.670 --> 07:58.880
I'm gonna be making
the decisions from now on.

07:58.880 --> 08:00.380
I'm gonna go to
the governing board.

08:00.380 --> 08:02.580
I'm gonna get Richard back in
and Minnick out.

08:02.580 --> 08:04.670
I'm going over your head.

08:04.670 --> 08:07.710
♪♪

08:23.120 --> 08:24.420
I don't understand.

08:24.420 --> 08:25.880
He's never been that interested
in the foundation.

08:25.880 --> 08:27.960
I know. He does not appreciate
our role or the scope of it.

08:27.960 --> 08:32.580
77 hospitals nationwide,
43 full-service clinics.

08:32.580 --> 08:34.750
Not to mention the Worldwide
Health Initiative.

08:34.750 --> 08:37.540
Oh. Somebody's been
doing her homework.

08:37.540 --> 08:38.960
I've just been curious.

08:38.960 --> 08:41.920
Or maybe you just like
being in charge.

08:41.920 --> 08:43.670
You know, the thing is,

08:43.670 --> 08:46.000
I was good at that job.
-Mm-hmm.

08:46.000 --> 08:48.960
I like doing that stuff --
the admin work, the scheduling.

08:48.960 --> 08:50.880
Meredith
doesn't even like it.

08:50.880 --> 08:54.540
You know, I want you to see the
Avery Trauma Center in Chicago.

08:54.540 --> 08:56.120
They do things very differently
than you do here.

08:56.120 --> 08:57.620
We should go.

08:57.620 --> 08:59.120
Ab-- Absolutely. I'd love to see
how they run things.

08:59.120 --> 09:02.080
No, honey. I want them to see
how you run things.

09:02.080 --> 09:04.080
[ Siren wailing ]
-Oh, yeah, I-I'd love that.

09:04.080 --> 09:06.830
Thank you.
-Trauma 1.

09:06.830 --> 09:09.080
-What do we got?
-Turkey-fryer accident.

09:09.080 --> 09:10.790
Propane tank exploded,
blew shrapnel everywhere.

09:10.790 --> 09:12.080
His family's behind him --

09:12.080 --> 09:13.710
minor injuries,
but he caught the brunt of it --

09:13.710 --> 09:15.000
full-thickness burns
to the neck,

09:15.000 --> 09:16.290
down the left side
of his body,

09:16.290 --> 09:17.960
extending
into the perineum,

09:17.960 --> 09:19.120
left leg
partially de-gloved.

09:19.120 --> 09:21.250
One, two, three.

09:21.250 --> 09:24.290
♪♪

09:26.750 --> 09:28.210
Man: All right,
check on that gauze.

09:28.210 --> 09:30.250
-Oh, wow.
-Ohh.

09:30.250 --> 09:31.920
His bowel is eviscerated.

09:31.920 --> 09:34.380
I need to examine this wound
and the perineal burn.

09:34.380 --> 09:37.830
-Somebody call plastics!
-On it!

09:37.830 --> 09:39.330
Yeah.

09:39.330 --> 09:41.420
So, this kid definitely
has HLHS.

09:41.420 --> 09:43.170
Start him on a PGE.

09:43.170 --> 09:44.670
Labs are back.

09:44.670 --> 09:46.750
All righty, Gus, let's take
a look at your labs.

09:46.750 --> 09:48.500
Oh, they landed on Gus,
huh?

09:48.500 --> 09:50.210
How did the O.B.
not catch this?

09:50.210 --> 09:52.000
Okay, DeLuca, we need to get him
on the transplant list, ASAP.

09:52.000 --> 09:54.460
No. Hold on.

09:54.460 --> 09:56.790
No.
We're gonna do a Norwood.

09:56.790 --> 09:58.790
I don't think so.
He has mitral valve regurg.

09:58.790 --> 10:00.250
I don't think the little kid
can survive

10:00.250 --> 10:01.710
a full reconstruction
like that.

10:01.710 --> 10:04.250
I know he won't survive the wait
for a newborn donor heart.

10:04.250 --> 10:06.580
He's stable for now.
He can tolerate a Norwood.

10:06.580 --> 10:08.540
So, what's next?

10:08.540 --> 10:09.920
Parents are freaking out.
We go talk to them next.

10:09.920 --> 10:12.960
♪♪

10:15.210 --> 10:16.210
[ PA chatter ]

10:16.210 --> 10:17.460
[ Telephone ringing ]

10:17.460 --> 10:18.380
Where did they
take Dad?

10:18.380 --> 10:19.670
Let me check you out.

10:19.670 --> 10:21.080
It's okay, Pammy.
It's gonna be okay.

10:21.080 --> 10:24.250
Your fiancé just deep-fried
our father. That is not okay.

10:24.250 --> 10:25.500
This is from
a turkey fryer?

10:25.500 --> 10:26.920
It's the one thing
I know how to cook.

10:26.920 --> 10:28.670
I-I-I was just trying to do
something special.

10:28.670 --> 10:30.170
You mean unforgettable,

10:30.170 --> 10:31.750
like that time
you killed my dad?

10:31.750 --> 10:33.040
Pam, come on.
He didn't mean to.

10:33.040 --> 10:34.880
Rodney,
Dad's leg melted off.

10:34.880 --> 10:36.210
You have no eyebrows.

10:36.210 --> 10:38.500
I'm so sorry, honey.
I'm so sorry.
I know.

10:38.500 --> 10:39.960
Your arm has
a partial-thickness burn.

10:39.960 --> 10:41.500
You'll need to learn to dress it
while it heals.

10:41.500 --> 10:43.250
I can help.
How can I help?

10:43.250 --> 10:44.580
Oh, I don't know.

10:44.580 --> 10:45.710
Go back in time,
when I told you,

10:45.710 --> 10:47.620
"Deep fryers are dumb,"
and listen to me!

10:47.620 --> 10:50.170
Can you tell me
how my father is?

10:50.170 --> 10:51.330
Pam, I'm sorry.

10:51.330 --> 10:53.580
Maybe
just stop talking.

10:53.580 --> 10:55.460
Someone will come
dress those burns,

10:55.460 --> 10:56.960
and I'll go
get an update.

10:56.960 --> 10:59.830
♪♪

11:01.250 --> 11:03.330
All right, he's got a lot of
neck swelling.

11:03.330 --> 11:05.460
Can you get me a fiber-optic
scope just in case?

11:05.460 --> 11:07.460
This wound extends deep.
The bladder is destroyed.

11:07.460 --> 11:09.210
I need to get him in an O.R.
for a repair.

11:09.210 --> 11:11.250
Uh, no, you can do
the bladder repair later.

11:11.250 --> 11:13.710
I need to do an ex-lap with
an abdominal washout first.

11:13.710 --> 11:15.380
Yeah, I can't even see
his vocal cords.

11:15.380 --> 11:17.290
-Here. Let me try.
-No, I got it. I got it.

11:17.290 --> 11:18.790
Warren,
call up to the O.R.

11:18.790 --> 11:20.750
Tell them to place the patient
in a lithotomy position

11:20.750 --> 11:22.710
for a perineal evaluation.

11:22.710 --> 11:24.710
Warren, let them know we need
a perc nephrostomy setup

11:24.710 --> 11:26.830
and a possible ileal conduit
for reconstruction.

11:26.830 --> 11:28.580
His small bowel is sticking out
of his abdomen.

11:28.580 --> 11:30.080
What ileal conduit
are you talking about?

11:30.080 --> 11:32.540
Jackson, the tendon is exposed.
He's gonna need a skin flap.

11:32.540 --> 11:34.580
-No, no, no, that can wait.
-I'm just saying --

11:34.580 --> 11:36.460
I know when flap coverage is
warranted and when it isn't.

11:36.460 --> 11:38.960
And another bickering family.
Fantastic.

11:38.960 --> 11:40.120
Warren,
did you say something?

11:40.120 --> 11:41.750
Uh, I said I'm gonna
go book an O.R.

11:41.750 --> 11:42.960
-Okay, well, hop to it, then.
-Well, hurry up, then.

11:42.960 --> 11:44.040
-Get going, child.
-Come on. Let's get this.

11:45.380 --> 11:47.120
Sister Agnes
is good to go.

11:47.120 --> 11:48.540
It went great.

11:48.540 --> 11:50.880
In, out, no problem.

11:50.880 --> 11:52.040
Feels good to be back,
huh?

11:52.040 --> 11:53.830
Yeah.

11:53.830 --> 11:55.710
Back at work.

11:57.380 --> 11:59.380
I'm still not ready
to see Owen.

11:59.380 --> 12:02.540
I just, uh, don't know
what I would say to him.

12:02.540 --> 12:03.920
Okay, well,
I'm just riffing here,

12:03.920 --> 12:07.040
but you could start with
"Hi, Owen."

12:09.620 --> 12:10.620
Sorry.

12:10.620 --> 12:13.040
When you're ready.
No judgment.

12:13.040 --> 12:14.500
Uh, could you just check the
hall so I can get out of here?

12:14.500 --> 12:16.290
Yes, of course.
Okay.

12:16.290 --> 12:21.250
♪♪

12:21.250 --> 12:22.210
-All clear.
-Okay.

12:22.210 --> 12:24.670
Go. Go. Go.

12:24.670 --> 12:26.920
[ Monitors beeping ]

12:26.920 --> 12:29.210
It's called Hypoplastic
Left Heart Syndrome.

12:29.210 --> 12:32.120
The left side of Gus' heart
is underdeveloped,

12:32.120 --> 12:35.330
so it can't deliver oxygenated
blood to the rest of his body.

12:35.330 --> 12:36.620
Okay, so,
what do we do now?

12:36.620 --> 12:38.080
He'll need surgery?

12:38.080 --> 12:40.080
There are two options --
a heart transplant

12:40.080 --> 12:42.580
or an open-heart surgery
to reconstruct Gus' heart,

12:42.580 --> 12:44.750
called a Norwood.
I think we go with that.

12:44.750 --> 12:46.830
And I think that
we should consider

12:46.830 --> 12:48.540
waiting for
the heart transplant.

12:48.540 --> 12:50.040
I'm concerned that
your little guy

12:50.040 --> 12:52.380
doesn't have the strength to
withstand a staged procedure.

12:52.380 --> 12:54.170
A staged procedure?

12:54.170 --> 12:56.830
Yeah, the Norwood is the first
of three separate surgeries

12:56.830 --> 12:58.790
that are performed over the
first three years of his life,

12:58.790 --> 13:00.580
as opposed to just one
for the transplant.

13:00.580 --> 13:02.330
But with a heart
like Gus',

13:02.330 --> 13:03.750
the wait could be
more time than he has.

13:03.750 --> 13:05.170
Also, you're looking at
a lifetime

13:05.170 --> 13:06.580
of anti-rejection drugs.

13:06.580 --> 13:09.460
As opposed to the strain of
multiple surgeries,

13:09.460 --> 13:11.750
often resulting in a transplant
in the long run, anyway.

13:11.750 --> 13:13.420
And in Gus' case,
we have a bit of time

13:13.420 --> 13:15.080
before his symptoms
become intolerable.

13:15.080 --> 13:16.380
I'm not willing to
accept that risk.

13:16.380 --> 13:17.710
Okay, but he --

13:17.710 --> 13:19.500
he says that Gus won't survive
your thing, the --

13:19.500 --> 13:22.040
-Norwood. And I think he can.
-Yeah, but he's a heart surgeon.

13:22.040 --> 13:23.460
And I operate on babies
all the time.

13:23.460 --> 13:25.040
I've seen more of these cases
than he has.

13:25.040 --> 13:26.290
I know how well they do.

13:26.290 --> 13:27.960
Also, I'd rather
invest in a sure thing

13:27.960 --> 13:30.620
than wait for a donor
that might not show up in time.

13:30.620 --> 13:31.670
Okay, so, you're just saying
that there's a poss--

13:31.670 --> 13:33.790
Okay, well, then just tell us
what to do.

13:33.790 --> 13:36.460
My baby is dying, and I don't
know how to help him.

13:36.460 --> 13:39.790
You're just confusing us.
Just, what do we do?

13:39.790 --> 13:44.460
♪♪

13:44.460 --> 13:46.210
I...

13:48.290 --> 13:50.210
I-I think that we should
just go with

13:50.210 --> 13:52.080
the transplant.
-Norwood.

13:55.580 --> 14:00.330
Um...you said that
we have some time, right?

14:04.920 --> 14:06.210
What the hell, man?

14:06.210 --> 14:07.750
They're overwhelmed.
They just had a baby.

14:07.750 --> 14:09.540
What, so they shouldn't
hear the whole story?

14:09.540 --> 14:10.830
They don't need to hear you
argue with me.

14:10.830 --> 14:12.000
Well, you should have
heard me out

14:12.000 --> 14:13.080
before you went
running in there.

14:13.080 --> 14:14.920
There's nothing to hear.
He's my patient.

14:14.920 --> 14:16.250
He's a good candidate
for a Norwood.

14:16.250 --> 14:18.000
-Well, I disagree.
-Or at least he is now.

14:18.000 --> 14:21.040
He might not be once they spend
a bunch of time deciding.

14:21.040 --> 14:22.670
DeLuca, let me know
when they're ready.

14:22.670 --> 14:26.830
♪♪

14:26.830 --> 14:28.620
Call UNOS.

14:28.620 --> 14:30.830
Put that kid on
the cardiac transplant list.

14:30.830 --> 14:33.210
I-I think Dr. Karev's really
into the Norwood idea.

14:33.210 --> 14:34.880
Yeah, well, Dr. Karev's not
making the decision.

14:34.880 --> 14:35.880
The parents are.

14:35.880 --> 14:37.500
And when they decide
on a transplant,

14:37.500 --> 14:39.170
I don't want to have missed out
on a heart because we waited.

14:39.170 --> 14:40.830
Just put him on the list.

14:40.830 --> 14:42.790
And don't tell Karev.
I don't want to hear about it.

14:42.790 --> 14:45.620
♪♪

15:00.710 --> 15:01.960
Jackson: The bladder isn't
the only thing at stake.

15:01.960 --> 15:03.080
-That's why I'm saying...
-I'm saying we can...

15:03.080 --> 15:04.380
The patient's prepped.

15:04.380 --> 15:05.710
No. We delay soft-tissue
coverage, period.

15:05.710 --> 15:06.460
It's a Gustilo type three.
It's an obvious fix-and-flap.

15:06.460 --> 15:08.330
Not in a dirty wound
like this.

15:08.330 --> 15:10.170
We need to do
a delayed reconstruction,

15:10.170 --> 15:11.210
not a primary
bladder repair.

15:11.210 --> 15:12.380
No. Reconstruction
should happen now...

15:12.380 --> 15:13.750
We have a penetrating wound
to explore.

15:13.750 --> 15:14.920
...before the tissues
become edematous.

15:14.920 --> 15:17.330
Okay, what about this?

15:17.330 --> 15:19.040
Webber and Kepner
explore the wound

15:19.040 --> 15:20.620
as Avery evaluates the burns

15:20.620 --> 15:21.670
to determine the need
for more coverage.

15:21.670 --> 15:24.040
The other Avery can do
a perineal evaluation,

15:24.040 --> 15:25.460
and after a full assessment,

15:25.460 --> 15:27.580
it'll become clear
how to proceed.

15:27.580 --> 15:31.880
♪♪

15:31.880 --> 15:33.880
I jus-- You know,
Minnick said that

15:33.880 --> 15:36.420
we should work
the problem with you.

15:36.420 --> 15:38.830
Actually, Warren,
that should work.

15:38.830 --> 15:40.120
Thank you.

15:40.120 --> 15:43.170
♪♪

15:48.000 --> 15:49.580
[ Indistinct conversations ]

15:52.460 --> 15:53.790
What?

15:53.790 --> 15:55.830
You called it
with Riggs.

15:55.830 --> 15:57.670
-What do you mean?
-The guy's a snake.

15:57.670 --> 15:59.040
I didn't say that.

15:59.040 --> 16:00.500
Look,
he just made a mom cry.

16:00.500 --> 16:01.710
Well,
her kid's in the hospital.

16:01.710 --> 16:03.290
There's a high probability
of tears.

16:03.290 --> 16:04.830
He thinks he's a cardio god
or something,

16:04.830 --> 16:06.420
like he knows everything.

16:06.420 --> 16:07.790
When I'm the peds guy,
I know things --

16:07.790 --> 16:09.250
if he would just listen.

16:09.250 --> 16:11.420
The guy's a total snake,
just like you said.

16:11.420 --> 16:14.830
Well, I definitely
never said that.

16:14.830 --> 16:16.790
[ Indistinct talking
over P.A. system ]

16:16.790 --> 16:18.250
Oh! Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
You're back!

16:18.250 --> 16:21.000
-Oh, actually --
-Ahh! I'm so happy! [ Laughs ]

16:21.000 --> 16:22.920
Oh! Dr. Minnick's method
is awesome,

16:22.920 --> 16:24.210
but I've really been
wanting to do it with you.

16:24.210 --> 16:25.620
-Edwards --
-And I -- Uh, wait.

16:25.620 --> 16:26.880
Stop. Hey.

16:26.880 --> 16:28.380
Are you anti-Minnick?
Please don't be anti-Minnick.

16:28.380 --> 16:29.620
-Stephanie!
-What? What?

16:29.620 --> 16:31.040
I'm not here.
You didn't see me.

16:31.040 --> 16:33.120
Oh. Oh.

16:33.120 --> 16:34.380
Would you mind just
walking through the E.R.

16:34.380 --> 16:35.960
to see if Owen is in there?

16:35.960 --> 16:37.750
-No.
-Thank you.

16:37.750 --> 16:39.670
No. I mean, "No."

16:39.670 --> 16:41.500
I have to work.

16:41.500 --> 16:43.790
I don't want to get dragged
into your marriage again.

16:43.790 --> 16:45.120
You know, boundaries.

16:45.120 --> 16:46.880
Right.

16:46.880 --> 16:48.620
Of course.
-Sorry.

16:48.620 --> 16:50.540
Come back!

16:50.540 --> 16:52.580
Okay, bye.
-Okay.

16:54.540 --> 16:57.040
-Hi!
-Hi yourself.

16:57.040 --> 16:58.830
How big is your stove?

16:58.830 --> 17:00.460
I don't -- I don't
know how to answer that.

17:00.460 --> 17:02.540
I want to make pierogi for you,
but my stove sucks.

17:02.540 --> 17:04.080
Ooh, that sounds nice.
Uh, what is it?

17:04.080 --> 17:05.460
Something I do very well.

17:05.460 --> 17:07.040
Okay.

17:07.040 --> 17:08.420
I don't have to stay
or anything.

17:08.420 --> 17:11.830
Just...pierogi.

17:11.830 --> 17:15.250
Jak posmakujesz moje pierogi,
to nie bedziesz chciala innych.

17:15.250 --> 17:17.540
I have no idea
what you just said,

17:17.540 --> 17:19.920
but I'd like you to say
much more of it.

17:19.920 --> 17:21.210
-I'll see you around 8:00.
-Okay.

17:21.210 --> 17:24.000
-I'll bring everything.
-Okay.

17:28.040 --> 17:29.920
Let's divide this segment,

17:29.920 --> 17:32.540
and then I'll prepare for
diverting colostomy.

17:32.540 --> 17:34.120
No.
Instead, actually, I think

17:34.120 --> 17:36.170
we can do the primary
bowel repair right here.

17:36.170 --> 17:38.880
Kepner, you're no longer running
General Surgery,

17:38.880 --> 17:40.210
so how about
you let me do my job?

17:40.210 --> 17:41.830
But she is
running this case.

17:41.830 --> 17:43.250
She brought in the trauma.

17:43.250 --> 17:44.830
Her department,
her patient.

17:44.830 --> 17:46.620
[ Monitors beeping ]

17:51.210 --> 17:54.250
3-oh vicryl for
bowel anastomosis.

17:54.250 --> 17:56.290
I checked my calendar
for Chicago,

17:56.290 --> 17:58.500
and I'm pretty booked
for the first two weeks,

17:58.500 --> 18:00.960
but the weekend of the 25th
might work.

18:00.960 --> 18:02.120
Yeah. Sounds good.
All right.

18:02.120 --> 18:03.830
There's an architectural
boat tour.

18:03.830 --> 18:05.420
Ben: Oh, I've done that.

18:05.420 --> 18:07.000
It sounds boring,
but it's actually fascinating.

18:07.000 --> 18:08.670
-Oh, fun.
-What is happening?

18:08.670 --> 18:10.170
Weekend of the 25th,
I'll be out of town,

18:10.170 --> 18:11.170
so you'll have Harriet.

18:11.170 --> 18:12.710
Ah.
You two taking a vacation?

18:12.710 --> 18:14.000
It is not a vacation.

18:14.000 --> 18:15.250
You're taking a boat tour, Mom.

18:15.250 --> 18:16.580
Ben:
If you're going to Chicago,

18:16.580 --> 18:18.960
you really have to take
that boat tour. It's...

18:20.380 --> 18:22.580
We're visiting
the Avery Trauma Center there.

18:22.580 --> 18:24.420
Richard: Trauma Center?
Why's that?

18:24.420 --> 18:26.750
Is our trauma program
next on your chopping block?

18:29.880 --> 18:32.960
I'm also getting us
"Hamilton" tickets.

18:32.960 --> 18:34.620
Yay!

18:34.620 --> 18:36.500
You're going to "Hamilton"
without me?

18:36.500 --> 18:39.040
[ Monitors beeping ]

18:41.380 --> 18:43.250
[ Indistinct talking
over P.A. system ]

18:44.830 --> 18:48.210
Heya.
Ugh. I'm starving.

18:48.210 --> 18:49.290
I've been in this

18:49.290 --> 18:51.250
complex sarcoma excision
for seven hours.

18:51.250 --> 18:53.120
And guess who got to
dissect the tumor

18:53.120 --> 18:54.420
from the vascular
structure.

18:54.420 --> 18:55.670
That's right.
[ Slurps ]

18:55.670 --> 18:57.000
Me.

18:59.960 --> 19:01.420
What's wrong?
Is there something wrong?

19:01.420 --> 19:04.920
No. I, uh...

19:04.920 --> 19:07.580
It's just, I'm on a case
with two attendings

19:07.580 --> 19:08.960
who want
different treatments

19:08.960 --> 19:10.620
and have given me
competing instructions,

19:10.620 --> 19:14.380
and [sighs]
I don't know what to do.

19:16.620 --> 19:19.080
Well, you'll make
the right choice.

19:19.080 --> 19:21.290
You always do.

19:21.290 --> 19:24.880
♪♪

19:24.880 --> 19:26.290
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

19:26.290 --> 19:28.290
[ Sighs ]
I got to go.

19:39.500 --> 19:41.830
[ Sighs ]

19:42.670 --> 19:45.880
[ Siren wailing ]

19:45.880 --> 19:48.920
Incoming MCC.
I'm on it.

19:48.920 --> 19:51.960
♪♪

19:57.120 --> 19:59.080
-MCC?
-Unhelmeted.

19:59.080 --> 20:01.330
GCS of 4,
intubated on the scene.

20:01.330 --> 20:02.670
He's got
an open-skull fracture.

20:02.670 --> 20:03.880
-Conscious at the scene?
-No.

20:03.880 --> 20:05.790
He has decorticate posturing.
Page neuro now.

20:07.290 --> 20:08.420
Neuro's here.

20:08.420 --> 20:10.620
[ Radio chatter ]

20:10.620 --> 20:12.880
Let's go. Let's go.

20:12.880 --> 20:15.920
♪♪

20:18.960 --> 20:21.620
Minnick's method doesn't just
get residents up to speed.

20:21.620 --> 20:22.920
It gets them there faster.

20:22.920 --> 20:24.710
Faster isn't better
unless you're cutting corners

20:24.710 --> 20:26.080
or creating
some kind of factory.

20:26.080 --> 20:28.290
-I'm doing no such thing.
-In your opinion.

20:28.290 --> 20:29.670
You know what?
This stitch that I just did --

20:29.670 --> 20:31.880
no one else does it like this,
and do you know why?

20:31.880 --> 20:34.170
'Cause Mark Sloan took the time
to teach me how to do it,

20:34.170 --> 20:35.880
'cause I watched him
and I watched him

20:35.880 --> 20:37.380
and I learned from him,

20:37.380 --> 20:38.960
much in the same way
so many surgeons

20:38.960 --> 20:41.880
have learned from Dr. Webber,
learned from his artistry.

20:41.880 --> 20:44.120
And you're telling me what,
those days are over?

20:44.120 --> 20:45.830
Dr. Webber
makes artists here.

20:45.830 --> 20:47.460
Dr. Minnick
makes robots.

20:47.460 --> 20:48.750
Three-oh silk, please.

20:48.750 --> 20:50.500
Bringing Dr. Minnick here
was not the right call.

20:50.500 --> 20:51.830
Okay, you know what?

20:51.830 --> 20:54.290
To be clear, that particular
decision was made by Bailey.

20:54.290 --> 20:55.380
Isn't that right, Warren?

20:55.380 --> 20:56.830
Let's just
leave me out of this.

20:56.830 --> 20:58.210
Even if
Minnick's program was good,

20:58.210 --> 21:00.080
the way you two went about
implementing the entire thing

21:00.080 --> 21:02.170
had zero respect for the history
of this institution,

21:02.170 --> 21:04.250
certainly no respect
for Dr. Webber.

21:04.250 --> 21:07.080
Jackson, that's okay.
I mean, are you really telling
me this is good management, Mom?

21:07.080 --> 21:08.420
You think this is good
for morale?

21:08.420 --> 21:10.080
Maybe if you hadn't
talked the entire staff

21:10.080 --> 21:12.670
into forming a coup,
you might have listened.

21:12.670 --> 21:14.040
The patient getting
coagulopathic.

21:14.040 --> 21:15.580
Mayo scissors.
And you know what?

21:15.580 --> 21:17.380
You have no clue
about management.

21:17.380 --> 21:18.960
Oh, I almost forgot you got
a new minion in the deal.

21:18.960 --> 21:21.540
Oh, come on.
What is it you want to learn
from my mom exactly --

21:21.540 --> 21:23.920
how to get an entire hospital to
turn against you in a day or --

21:23.920 --> 21:25.460
Jackson, stop it!
Just stop it!

21:25.460 --> 21:28.290
You keep saying,
"I'm an Avery, I'm an Avery,"

21:28.290 --> 21:31.040
but you're not, not in the way
you're trying to be.

21:31.040 --> 21:33.580
A title
doesn't mean anything.

21:33.580 --> 21:36.420
It's the person
who owns it.

21:36.420 --> 21:39.920
Yes, I took your father's name,
but it's what I did with it.

21:39.920 --> 21:42.250
It's what I made with it.
That's what matters.

21:42.250 --> 21:44.880
You?

21:44.880 --> 21:48.670
You are
an outstanding surgeon.

21:48.670 --> 21:51.710
♪♪

21:54.750 --> 21:57.460
[ Exhales sharply ]

21:57.460 --> 21:58.920
[ Clears throat ]

21:58.920 --> 22:00.040
[ Sighs ]

22:00.040 --> 22:03.330
♪♪

22:03.330 --> 22:06.380
He's too far gone for us to do
anything more tonight.

22:06.380 --> 22:09.710
We should take him to the ICU,
start fresh tomorrow.

22:09.710 --> 22:11.380
Agreed?
-Yeah.

22:11.380 --> 22:12.750
[ All murmuring ]

22:23.920 --> 22:25.380
Those sutures should
control the bleeding,

22:25.380 --> 22:27.040
but he's got a big
open-skull fracture up here.

22:27.040 --> 22:28.500
-FAST exam negative.
-Pupils are sluggish.

22:31.290 --> 22:33.250
I didn't realize
you were back.

22:33.250 --> 22:34.620
There's no other
obvious injuries.

22:34.620 --> 22:36.040
I'm gonna need to see
those trauma films.

22:36.040 --> 22:38.670
I just stopped by for,
uh, some stuff.

22:38.670 --> 22:40.540
-Stuff?
-Stuff.

22:40.540 --> 22:42.040
I was shopping,
odds and ends.

22:42.040 --> 22:44.460
I needed floss and realized
I had a bunch here.

22:44.460 --> 22:45.830
Then this guy pulled up.

22:45.830 --> 22:47.250
Positive Babinski.

22:47.250 --> 22:48.620
Floss.

22:48.620 --> 22:50.250
Can't sleep without it.

22:50.250 --> 22:51.960
Yeah. I know.

22:51.960 --> 22:53.170
[ Knock on door ]
Stephanie: Labs are back.

22:53.170 --> 22:54.460
Trauma...films are clear.

22:54.460 --> 22:55.920
Thank you, Edwards.

22:55.920 --> 22:57.620
Uh, page someone from neuro,
please.

22:57.620 --> 23:00.290
What? Why? [ Stammers ]
It's fine. I'm -- I'm --

23:00.290 --> 23:01.670
Well, this looks like it's gonna
be an uphill climb,

23:01.670 --> 23:03.040
and if you're not
actually back...

23:03.040 --> 23:04.920
Owen, stop. Edwards,
show me the skull fracture.

23:13.290 --> 23:16.500
I just spent the day
trapped on a case

23:16.500 --> 23:19.880
with my wife
and Jackson and April.

23:19.880 --> 23:23.000
-Yikes.
-Yeah. So, if I may,

23:23.000 --> 23:25.420
I would love to take you up
on your offer, after all,

23:25.420 --> 23:28.540
and stay at your place,
enjoy some good company,

23:28.540 --> 23:29.750
and get a good night's sleep.

23:29.750 --> 23:31.380
Oh, okay.
Uh, t-tonight?

23:31.380 --> 23:32.830
If the offer hasn't expired.

23:32.830 --> 23:35.290
Yeah. Well, I mean, I have
a date now, but I can cancel it.

23:35.290 --> 23:36.580
-Oh, no, no, no, don't. No.
-No, no, I can. I can.

23:36.580 --> 23:38.750
Listen.
[ Stammering ]

23:38.750 --> 23:40.210
I just made it today.

23:40.210 --> 23:42.290
And I-I probably shouldn't
be doing it, anyway,

23:42.290 --> 23:43.710
so I can cancel.

23:43.710 --> 23:45.290
No.
I wouldn't dream of it.

23:45.290 --> 23:47.000
You go have fun, all right?
-Are you sure?

23:47.000 --> 23:48.880
Yeah. I've got a patient
who's touch-and-go.

23:48.880 --> 23:50.460
I should probably stick around
here, anyway.

23:50.460 --> 23:52.880
So, um, give me the dirt
tomorrow.

23:52.880 --> 23:54.710
[ Chuckles ]

23:57.380 --> 23:59.710
[ Beeping ]

24:04.000 --> 24:06.460
Oh.
You're still here.

24:06.460 --> 24:08.040
Still here?

24:08.040 --> 24:10.960
Uh,
I got pulled onto a case.

24:10.960 --> 24:12.080
Oh, okay.

24:12.080 --> 24:13.960
Well, Sister Agnes
is recovering well.

24:13.960 --> 24:15.580
Her neuro scans are perfect.

24:15.580 --> 24:17.080
Great job.
-Thanks.

24:17.080 --> 24:18.580
Thank you for coming in
this morning.

24:18.580 --> 24:20.790
No problem.
Thanks, Pierce.

24:24.880 --> 24:27.080
So, you've been here
since morning?

24:27.080 --> 24:28.540
[ Computer beeping ]
Look at that.

24:28.540 --> 24:31.500
The scans are up and...

24:31.500 --> 24:34.040
[ Beeping continues ]

24:37.250 --> 24:39.460
Hey. First day back
and pulling an all-nighter.

24:39.460 --> 24:41.330
Ambitious.

24:41.330 --> 24:42.920
[ Telephone rings ]

24:42.920 --> 24:46.000
What's going on?

24:46.000 --> 24:48.170
Why are you
being a jerk?

24:48.170 --> 24:49.830
What?

24:49.830 --> 24:51.540
Alex said
you were being a jerk.

24:51.540 --> 24:53.000
Ugh. Of course.
He tattled.

24:53.000 --> 24:55.460
Let me make something
very clear to you.

24:55.460 --> 24:57.670
If you want to get anywhere
with me,

24:57.670 --> 25:00.170
messing with Alex
is not the way.

25:00.170 --> 25:02.420
Do not contradict him
in front of patients.

25:02.420 --> 25:04.420
And please don't speak to him
like he's an idiot.

25:04.420 --> 25:05.960
Back it up. Get --
Get anywhere with you?

25:05.960 --> 25:07.880
So, you admit it?
-Admit what?

25:07.880 --> 25:09.290
That there's somewhere
to get with you.

25:09.290 --> 25:11.500
Don't change the subject.
I'm talking about Alex.

25:11.500 --> 25:14.000
Karev is pissed because
I'm giving a really sick baby

25:14.000 --> 25:17.000
a chance at a miracle.
He's giving it a Band-Aid.

25:17.000 --> 25:18.830
Maybe he just wants to
play it safe. I don't know.

25:18.830 --> 25:20.380
But whatever it is,
I really don't care.

25:20.380 --> 25:22.170
-Why don't you care?
-Because I'm right,

25:22.170 --> 25:24.290
and I don't have to
keep justifying...

25:24.290 --> 25:25.920
Forget it.

25:25.920 --> 25:27.580
Wait. Where are you going?
We're having a conversation.

25:27.580 --> 25:29.120
Nah. I'm done.

25:29.120 --> 25:30.420
So, you're just gonna
walk away?

25:30.420 --> 25:32.620
Damn right!
I'm a jerk!

25:32.620 --> 25:37.500
♪♪

25:37.500 --> 25:40.080
But when your father
began to decompensate...

25:40.080 --> 25:43.750
We decided to hit pause,
give him some time to rest

25:43.750 --> 25:45.620
and get stronger
before we continue.

25:45.620 --> 25:47.330
God. Oh, God.

25:47.330 --> 25:48.620
Can we see him?

25:48.620 --> 25:49.960
"We"?
Who is "we"?

25:49.960 --> 25:51.210
Jim.

25:51.210 --> 25:54.040
I meant you guys,
obviously.

25:54.040 --> 25:55.500
Can they see him?

25:55.500 --> 25:56.960
That's not really a good idea,
Jim.

25:56.960 --> 25:58.580
He's not
out of the woods yet.

25:58.580 --> 26:01.830
I'd really like him to rest
so we can go back in tomorrow.

26:01.830 --> 26:03.420
Right now you guys should
just get some food,

26:03.420 --> 26:04.880
get some rest yourselves.

26:04.880 --> 26:07.330
No.
We aren't going anywhere.

26:07.330 --> 26:09.080
Tell you what --
you guys stay here,

26:09.080 --> 26:10.710
and I'll bring us in
some food.

26:10.710 --> 26:12.670
Food?

26:12.670 --> 26:14.880
You're gonna get us food?

26:14.880 --> 26:16.330
You?

26:16.330 --> 26:19.040
[ Voice breaking ]
Rodney...

26:19.040 --> 26:24.120
♪♪

26:24.120 --> 26:25.290
♪ Oh, Father, tell me ♪

26:25.290 --> 26:27.540
Maybe you should go.

26:27.540 --> 26:31.040
Sure.
♪ We get what we deserve ♪

26:31.040 --> 26:32.420
Okay.
I'll come back in a bit.

26:32.420 --> 26:33.750
Just shoot me a text and --
-No.

26:33.750 --> 26:35.500
♪ Oh, we get what we deserve ♪

26:35.500 --> 26:38.120
I know you meant well,
but my father is...

26:38.120 --> 26:40.330
I can't.

26:40.330 --> 26:42.040
It's all I'll ever think about
when I look at you.

26:42.040 --> 26:45.880
♪ And way down
we go, go, go, go, go ♪

26:45.880 --> 26:47.670
Oh.

26:47.670 --> 26:50.620
♪ And way down we go ♪

26:50.620 --> 26:53.420
-Oh, Rodney --
-I think you should just go.

26:53.420 --> 26:59.500
♪ Way down we go ♪

26:59.500 --> 27:03.580
♪ Way down we go ♪

27:03.580 --> 27:06.330
♪♪

27:06.330 --> 27:08.750
♪ Oh, you let your feet
run wild ♪

27:08.750 --> 27:11.040
Amelia: I mean, this guy's got
an epidural hematoma

27:11.040 --> 27:12.750
and diffuse axonal injury.

27:12.750 --> 27:15.710
Surgery may not help,
but we can try, obviously,

27:15.710 --> 27:17.960
even if it is
a lost cause.

27:17.960 --> 27:22.250
♪ Yeah, but for the fall,
ooh, my ♪

27:22.250 --> 27:24.960
You've been working,

27:24.960 --> 27:27.790
doing cases?

27:27.790 --> 27:29.790
No.

27:29.790 --> 27:33.420
♪ Oh, 'cause they will
run you down ♪

27:33.420 --> 27:35.750
Were you planning on
seeing me at all today?

27:35.750 --> 27:38.120
♪ Yes, and they will
run you down ♪

27:38.120 --> 27:39.580
No.

27:39.580 --> 27:42.420
So, you're just...
hiding.

27:42.420 --> 27:46.380
♪ And they will run you down,
down till you go ♪

27:46.380 --> 27:48.380
Is today your first time
coming in, or...?

27:48.380 --> 27:49.750
Yes.

27:49.750 --> 27:51.620
I-I-I came in
as a favor to Maggie.

27:51.620 --> 27:53.540
That's it.
[ Door opens ]

27:53.540 --> 27:55.120
The patient's prepped.
We're ready.

27:55.120 --> 27:58.290
♪ Way down we go ♪

27:58.290 --> 28:01.210
♪ Way down we go ♪

28:01.210 --> 28:02.120
You should leave.

28:02.120 --> 28:04.420
♪♪

28:04.420 --> 28:05.880
We're scrubbing in.

28:05.880 --> 28:07.670
You said it yourself --
it's a lost cause.

28:07.670 --> 28:10.710
♪ Ooh, ooh ♪

28:10.710 --> 28:13.000
Well, page another
trauma surgeon

28:13.000 --> 28:15.170
if you don't want to go in.
I'm going in.

28:15.170 --> 28:16.460
There are no lost causes.

28:16.460 --> 28:20.170
♪ Oh, way down we go ♪

28:29.420 --> 28:31.040
[ Door opens ]
I'm late. I know.

28:31.040 --> 28:32.580
Did I miss the window?

28:32.580 --> 28:34.830
No. No.
I'm good. I'm ready.

28:34.830 --> 28:36.580
Oh, no.

28:36.580 --> 28:38.710
You're tired.
-Why would you say that?

28:38.710 --> 28:41.040
'Cause you were sleeping
and because I'm tired.

28:41.040 --> 28:44.250
I'm so, so tired.

28:44.250 --> 28:47.620
I'm wiped. Ugh. Residents are
a bottomless pit of questions.

28:47.620 --> 28:50.380
And it's cute, but it's also
unbelievably draining.

28:50.380 --> 28:52.080
[ Yawning ] I know.

28:52.080 --> 28:54.880
Well, why don't we rest
a minute,

28:54.880 --> 28:56.920
like just for --
just for a minute?

28:56.920 --> 28:58.670
-Just a minute.
-Okay.

28:58.670 --> 29:00.040
-Then rally.
-Mm-hmm.

29:00.040 --> 29:00.920
One minute.

29:00.920 --> 29:03.790
45 seconds.

29:03.790 --> 29:06.290
♪♪

29:12.420 --> 29:14.750
[ Cellphone ringing ]

29:16.830 --> 29:18.380
Oh, my God.

29:18.380 --> 29:20.830
Oh, my God.

29:20.830 --> 29:22.040
Hello?

29:22.040 --> 29:24.120
Nathan: Seven.

29:24.120 --> 29:25.920
O.R. 7, if it's available.

29:25.920 --> 29:27.540
What's going on?

29:27.540 --> 29:28.960
I got good news --
great news.

29:28.960 --> 29:31.290
So, try not to
let it piss you off.
Just tell me.

29:31.290 --> 29:33.420
We got a heart for the Endris
baby, a perfect match.

29:33.420 --> 29:35.170
How?
He's not even on the list.

29:35.170 --> 29:36.750
Well,
I put him on the list.

29:36.750 --> 29:38.920
Without -- Without telling me?
Without the parents' consent?

29:38.920 --> 29:40.540
[ Sighs ]

29:40.540 --> 29:42.420
Did you know about this?

29:42.420 --> 29:44.670
Well, i-if he wasn't
on the list --

29:44.670 --> 29:47.250
Karev, this is a good thing,
okay?

29:47.250 --> 29:49.420
All we've got to do now is
have an awkward conversation

29:49.420 --> 29:51.960
with the parents,
and then we save a kid's life.

29:51.960 --> 29:54.040
You're unbelievable.

29:54.040 --> 29:55.500
You know that?

30:07.750 --> 30:10.620
I can talk to the family
with you.

30:10.620 --> 30:12.380
[ Sighs heavily ]

30:12.380 --> 30:14.540
Do you want
to be married to me?

30:14.540 --> 30:16.790
Yes.

30:16.790 --> 30:18.620
Then why won't you
talk to me?

30:20.960 --> 30:22.120
I'm not ready.

30:22.120 --> 30:23.790
For what?

30:23.790 --> 30:25.120
The fight.

30:25.120 --> 30:26.580
There doesn't
have to be one.

30:26.580 --> 30:28.500
There does. We are
on opposite sides of this.

30:28.500 --> 30:30.040
We both want completely
different things.

30:30.040 --> 30:32.620
We can't both have what we want,
so there will be a fight.

30:32.620 --> 30:35.000
And somebody
has to win.

30:37.120 --> 30:38.290
[ Sighs ]

30:38.290 --> 30:40.330
Or no one wins.

30:42.000 --> 30:43.880
I'll talk to the family.

30:50.210 --> 30:52.040
Hold on.

30:52.040 --> 30:54.790
This is why you called me all
the way in here at this hour?

30:54.790 --> 30:56.290
He went behind my back.
He lied to me.

30:56.290 --> 30:57.620
Hey, what's going on?
We ready?

30:57.620 --> 30:59.500
Hold on.
Look, I don't trust him.

30:59.500 --> 31:01.170
I don't want him
in the O.R. with me.

31:01.170 --> 31:02.960
Uh, what?

31:02.960 --> 31:04.920
Dr. Karev has
raised a complaint against you.

31:04.920 --> 31:06.880
-Oh, come on!
-He says that you've been --

31:06.880 --> 31:09.500
We had a disagreement about
treatment. That's all.

31:09.500 --> 31:11.580
He would have survived
the Norwood.
Or he wouldn't.

31:11.580 --> 31:13.330
Now we don't have to risk
killing him to find out.

31:13.330 --> 31:14.330
Nah. You just killed
some other kid

31:14.330 --> 31:15.580
by directing
that heart here.

31:15.580 --> 31:18.540
Congrats on that.
-All right! All right! Enough.

31:18.540 --> 31:22.380
The only fight here
is to keep this child alive,

31:22.380 --> 31:24.170
to fix his heart.

31:24.170 --> 31:26.120
You won.
You won that battle.

31:26.120 --> 31:27.460
Now finish
the freaking war.

31:27.460 --> 31:30.120
You two figure out a way
to work together long enough

31:30.120 --> 31:31.460
to put that heart
into that baby.

31:31.460 --> 31:33.710
Understood?

31:33.710 --> 31:36.330
[ Sampha's "(No One Knows Me)
Like the Piano" plays ]

31:39.710 --> 31:40.960
[ Heart monitor
beeping rapidly ]
What happened?

31:40.960 --> 31:42.080
Ben: Blood was seeping
out of the vac,

31:42.080 --> 31:43.210
and his pressure
was dropping,

31:43.210 --> 31:44.500
so they rushed him up here
to find the bleeder.

31:44.500 --> 31:45.790
Have lap pads ready.
-Whoa, whoa, whoa. What's --

31:45.790 --> 31:48.960
Got it.
I...got it.

31:48.960 --> 31:51.620
Sorry.
I was right here, so...

31:51.620 --> 31:53.750
No, no, no. Nice work, Warren.
You go ahead.

31:53.750 --> 31:55.000
Can you see the source
of the bleeding?

31:55.000 --> 31:56.380
Uh, yes, yes, I see it.

31:56.380 --> 31:57.750
It's, uh --
It's in the mesentery.

31:57.750 --> 31:59.250
Debakeys and a right angle,
please.

31:59.250 --> 32:02.040
Should I...keep going,
sir?

32:02.040 --> 32:06.250
♪ In my mother's home ♪

32:06.250 --> 32:07.540
Here.
I'll suction for you.

32:07.540 --> 32:08.790
Really?
The patient's a little unstable.

32:08.790 --> 32:10.330
You don't want to
take the lead?

32:10.330 --> 32:12.120
No. I don't think I need to.
I think Warren's got this.

32:12.120 --> 32:14.500
So, why are we even here?

32:14.500 --> 32:17.620
♪ Some people call a soul ♪

32:17.620 --> 32:20.040
Warren?

32:20.040 --> 32:21.250
Feel like you got this?

32:21.250 --> 32:22.880
Yes, sir.

32:22.880 --> 32:24.080
Two-oh silk, please.

32:24.080 --> 32:26.080
♪♪

32:26.080 --> 32:28.790
More laps.

32:28.790 --> 32:34.460
♪ Oh, you arrived
when I was 3 years old ♪

32:41.420 --> 32:44.380
♪ No one knows me
like the piano ♪

32:44.380 --> 32:46.080
You called UNOS
behind my back?

32:46.080 --> 32:47.170
I did.

32:47.170 --> 32:49.620
-I thought we were cool.
-We are.

32:49.620 --> 32:51.040
You went behind my back
when I specifically said --

32:51.040 --> 32:52.580
Look,
it's like you said.

32:52.580 --> 32:55.330
It's kids.

32:55.330 --> 33:02.210
♪ You know I left,
I flew the nest ♪

33:02.210 --> 33:09.920
♪ And you know I won't be long ♪

33:09.920 --> 33:17.250
♪ And in my chest
you know me best ♪

33:17.250 --> 33:24.880
♪ And you know
I'll be back home ♪

33:24.880 --> 33:26.920
[ Water running ]

33:29.710 --> 33:32.290
[ Water running ]

33:32.290 --> 33:34.670
So, what was that?

33:34.670 --> 33:36.210
Excuse me?

33:36.210 --> 33:38.330
You're just giving in
to this new way of teaching?

33:38.330 --> 33:39.880
I was teaching
a capable resident,

33:39.880 --> 33:42.420
same as I always have,
long before Minnick.

33:42.420 --> 33:45.670
No. No. In there, that was --
that was different.

33:45.670 --> 33:47.290
♪ And never let me go ♪

33:47.290 --> 33:49.380
Look, we can win this thing,
all right?

33:49.380 --> 33:51.040
There are strings
that I can pull, you know?

33:51.040 --> 33:52.580
I have a voice.
-Jackson, don't do it.

33:52.580 --> 33:54.420
It'll tear you
and your mother apart.

33:54.420 --> 33:56.750
Tear us apart? What about you?
You're her husband.

33:56.750 --> 33:58.000
You don't think this whole thing
is pushing you away?

33:58.000 --> 33:59.330
You don't know the first thing

33:59.330 --> 34:00.540
about my relationship
with your mother.

34:00.540 --> 34:02.750
And you don't know
my mother.

34:02.750 --> 34:04.420
I mean, you don't know
this is what she does.

34:04.420 --> 34:06.040
She finds a weakness,
and she exploits it.

34:06.040 --> 34:07.500
And she's gonna fight you.

34:07.500 --> 34:09.460
All the way here, she's gonna
fight and fight --

34:09.460 --> 34:11.790
We fell in love fighting over
this hospital.

34:11.790 --> 34:13.210
We'll be okay.

34:13.210 --> 34:15.380
Yeah, except she's not gonna
stop, all right?

34:15.380 --> 34:17.290
She's gonna fight
until she wins,

34:17.290 --> 34:19.500
no matter the cost.

34:19.500 --> 34:21.670
Don't let her.

34:21.670 --> 34:24.710
♪♪

34:28.750 --> 34:30.460
[ Door closes ]

34:42.830 --> 34:45.960
Well, your father's
out of surgery.

34:45.960 --> 34:48.620
His recovery is going to be
a long haul,

34:48.620 --> 34:49.670
but he will recover.

34:49.670 --> 34:51.290
Oh, thank God.

34:51.290 --> 34:52.960
I can take you
to see him.

34:54.830 --> 34:55.750
[ Keypad clicking ]

34:55.750 --> 34:57.250
What are you doing?

34:57.250 --> 35:00.580
It's just that...
Jim loves Dad.

35:00.580 --> 35:01.830
You're kidding, right?

35:01.830 --> 35:03.290
Pam,
it was an accident.

35:03.290 --> 35:05.880
Uh, which way?

35:05.880 --> 35:08.420
Ah.

35:08.420 --> 35:11.330
♪♪

35:35.380 --> 35:38.080
How could you do that?

35:38.080 --> 35:40.330
How can you do this
to somebody you care about?

35:40.330 --> 35:42.830
Jackson, you need to
stop this foolishness.

35:42.830 --> 35:44.330
What?
I just need to know.

35:44.330 --> 35:45.830
I need to know
if business is really

35:45.830 --> 35:47.290
that much more important to you
than family.

35:47.290 --> 35:48.960
This has nothing
to do with family.

35:48.960 --> 35:50.460
Of course it has to do
with family.

35:50.460 --> 35:54.000
Look, I get it, all right?
Business is business.

35:54.000 --> 35:57.210
If you need to fire someone
or replace them, do it.

35:57.210 --> 36:00.790
But if it's someone you love,
you just...

36:00.790 --> 36:02.750
Does that mean
nothing to you?

36:05.920 --> 36:08.460
Jackson, you and I
are two very different people.

36:08.460 --> 36:09.710
Yeah, no kidding.

36:09.710 --> 36:11.420
I've never been happier about
that fact in my life.

36:11.420 --> 36:14.580
You have never shown one ounce
of interest in this business.

36:14.580 --> 36:16.120
That's fine. Fine.

36:16.120 --> 36:17.920
Yeah, that's fine because
you have April now, right?

36:17.920 --> 36:19.920
Yeah, 'cause you finally
got that Avery

36:19.920 --> 36:21.170
that you always wished
that I was.

36:21.170 --> 36:23.120
No. No, son.

36:23.120 --> 36:24.960
No. You've always been
your own man.

36:24.960 --> 36:26.540
You've always
made your own way.

36:26.540 --> 36:29.540
Nothing could make a parent
more proud than that.

36:29.540 --> 36:32.250
Nothing.

36:32.250 --> 36:36.120
I am so happy
with who you are.

36:36.120 --> 36:38.250
I am.

36:38.250 --> 36:41.290
I just wish you were, too.

36:41.290 --> 36:44.880
♪♪

36:44.880 --> 36:46.420
[ Exhales sharply ]

36:57.790 --> 36:59.290
Saved the baby.

36:59.290 --> 37:00.670
Huh? Excuse me?

37:00.670 --> 37:03.710
The -- The baby, the one
that Karev and I were...

37:03.710 --> 37:04.960
Anyway,
the kid's alive.

37:04.960 --> 37:06.920
Oh, well,
that's great news.

37:06.920 --> 37:09.710
Okay. Now you're the one
being the jerk.

37:09.710 --> 37:12.040
Well, because Alex was right
about you.

37:12.040 --> 37:13.250
Oh, yes, of course,

37:13.250 --> 37:15.620
'cause everybody's
always in your ear,

37:15.620 --> 37:17.380
telling you what to
think about me.

37:17.380 --> 37:19.460
Maggie --
-Nobody tells me what to think.

37:19.460 --> 37:21.670
Okay, good, 'cause I don't want
their opinion, okay?

37:21.670 --> 37:22.880
I care about
what you think.

37:22.880 --> 37:24.960
About you? Actually,
I think a lot of things.

37:24.960 --> 37:27.880
No, no, no. No banter.
No more quips.

37:27.880 --> 37:30.460
I'll tell you
what I think.

37:30.460 --> 37:34.250
I think about you...

37:34.250 --> 37:36.750
a lot.

37:36.750 --> 37:38.500
Okay? I can't stop.

37:38.500 --> 37:41.040
And I'm telling you
I am in...

37:41.040 --> 37:42.250
if you are.

37:42.250 --> 37:44.880
I am in this.

37:44.880 --> 37:47.250
So, I'm just -- I'm just gonna
ask you outright.

37:47.250 --> 37:50.790
What do you think?

37:52.830 --> 37:55.120
Actually, don't answer.

37:55.120 --> 37:57.460
♪♪

37:57.460 --> 37:59.040
Not till you know.

38:02.750 --> 38:05.880
And when you do,
just give me a call.

38:05.880 --> 38:09.380
♪ They say sing what you know ♪

38:09.380 --> 38:12.290
♪ But I've sung what they want ♪

38:12.290 --> 38:14.960
♪ Some folks do
what they're told ♪

38:14.960 --> 38:17.040
What time is it?

38:17.040 --> 38:19.290
Did we fall asleep?

38:19.290 --> 38:20.620
I don't know.

38:20.620 --> 38:22.750
I feel rested.

38:22.750 --> 38:26.080
Oh, my God. That's because
it's almost morning.

38:26.080 --> 38:28.040
♪ Some things I've done before
I can't justify ♪

38:28.040 --> 38:31.120
So, I guess we just, uh,
spent the night together.

38:31.120 --> 38:33.920
♪ There are kings
in my past ♪
I guess we did.

38:33.920 --> 38:36.040
♪ Things no one
can be proud of ♪

38:36.040 --> 38:37.290
[ Chuckles ]

38:37.290 --> 38:39.250
[ Door opens ]
Oh, uh --

38:39.250 --> 38:40.540
Uh, sorry. Sorry.

38:40.540 --> 38:43.500
♪ And turn away from
any lack of love ♪

38:43.500 --> 38:47.420
♪ Oh, and I walked through
that door ♪

38:47.420 --> 38:49.250
♪ I say here I go ♪

38:49.250 --> 38:50.790
War isn't civil.

38:50.790 --> 38:52.170
♪ You see me and nothing more ♪

38:52.170 --> 38:53.920
You pick sides and defend them.

38:53.920 --> 38:55.710
You attack.

38:55.710 --> 38:59.920
♪ I know better ♪

38:59.920 --> 39:02.170
♪♪

39:02.170 --> 39:04.170
♪ I know better ♪

39:04.170 --> 39:05.540
You hurt people.

39:05.540 --> 39:07.710
You get hurt.

39:07.710 --> 39:09.080
How was it today?

39:09.080 --> 39:10.790
♪ Legend is just a name ♪

39:10.790 --> 39:12.380
Bad as you thought
it would be?

39:12.380 --> 39:14.670
Kind of.

39:14.670 --> 39:16.880
We need to talk.

39:16.880 --> 39:18.920
We have to, but...

39:18.920 --> 39:20.580
No, you don't.

39:20.580 --> 39:22.330
At least, not tonight.

39:22.330 --> 39:24.960
♪ I won't have to cut it off
from where it came ♪

39:24.960 --> 39:27.960
You weren't even supposed to
be here today. Come on.

39:27.960 --> 39:30.380
You fight...

39:30.380 --> 39:32.380
and you fight, and you fight.

39:32.380 --> 39:34.080
To what end?

39:34.080 --> 39:38.210
♪ This power and the color
of my face ♪

39:38.210 --> 39:40.170
♪ And I know better ♪

39:40.170 --> 39:42.290
Come home.

39:42.290 --> 39:44.210
♪ Oh, oh, oh ♪

39:44.210 --> 39:46.580
What are we fighting against?
♪ I know better ♪

39:46.580 --> 39:49.460
What are we fighting for?

39:49.460 --> 39:52.000
♪ Ohh, I'll rise
from the floor ♪

39:52.000 --> 39:53.710
Just get
a good night's sleep.

39:53.710 --> 39:55.790
♪ If I don't win ♪

39:55.790 --> 39:58.710
♪ I'll bust open that door,
so let me in ♪

39:58.710 --> 40:01.330
I never wanted to come between
the two of you...

40:01.330 --> 40:03.380
you and Jackson.

40:03.380 --> 40:05.920
I never wanted that.

40:05.920 --> 40:07.960
I know.

40:07.960 --> 40:11.330
When is it time to just quit
all this nonsense...

40:11.330 --> 40:15.960
♪ I know better ♪

40:15.960 --> 40:21.170
♪ Oh, I, I know better ♪

40:21.170 --> 40:24.330
♪ Yeah ♪

40:24.330 --> 40:27.120
♪ I know better ♪

40:27.120 --> 40:29.500
♪♪

40:29.500 --> 40:31.210
Well...

40:31.210 --> 40:34.460
good night.
♪ I know better ♪

40:34.460 --> 40:38.290
...and simply surrender?

40:38.290 --> 40:42.620
♪♪

40:42.620 --> 40:44.500
That is
one nasty throat tumor.

40:44.500 --> 40:45.710
Ugh, God.

40:45.710 --> 40:47.080
En bloc resection?

40:47.080 --> 40:49.710
Maybe. Maybe.

40:49.710 --> 40:53.120
Got a patient up at the, uh,
Avery hospital in Montana.

40:53.120 --> 40:55.210
[ Sighs ]

40:55.210 --> 40:57.250
I might have to go out there
for a consult.

40:59.580 --> 41:00.830
Huh.

41:00.830 --> 41:01.960
"Huh" what?

41:01.960 --> 41:04.040
I'm going to
an Avery hospital.

41:04.040 --> 41:05.960
Now you're going to
an Avery hospital.

41:05.960 --> 41:07.540
Oh, come on. Really?

41:07.540 --> 41:09.790
[ Scoffs ]
Yeah. It's not that.

41:09.790 --> 41:12.790
Are you -- Are you jealous?
Is that it?

41:12.790 --> 41:15.040
Jealous of my mom
manipulating you? No.

41:15.040 --> 41:17.540
Oh, stop.
[ Scoffs ]

41:17.540 --> 41:19.420
I'm not some puppet.

41:19.420 --> 41:21.000
I have my own brain.

41:21.000 --> 41:23.000
I have my own opinions.

41:23.000 --> 41:24.710
Working with your mom
and the foundation --

41:24.710 --> 41:26.380
it's full of opportunities
for me.

41:26.380 --> 41:28.540
And I get that you never wanted
that, and that's fine.

41:28.540 --> 41:30.670
But she sees
something in me.

41:30.670 --> 41:32.380
All right,
I'm going to bed.

41:34.250 --> 41:35.500
What is going on
with you?

41:35.500 --> 41:37.080
Nothing's going on with me.
Just leave it alone.

41:37.080 --> 41:38.330
Jackson, I --

41:38.330 --> 41:40.290
It's not your business.

41:43.460 --> 41:45.580
Good night.

41:49.290 --> 41:50.380
[ Door slams ]
